{"comments":"Pure PureScript implementation of SHA-256 (FIPS 180-4).\n\nThis implementation is designed for correctness and determinism, not speed.\nIt enables content hashing and UUID generation without any JavaScript FFI,\nensuring reproducible hashes across all environments.\n\n## Why Pure SHA-256?\n\nAt billion-agent scale, agents need deterministic identity:\n- Same content → same hash (always)\n- No platform-specific behavior\n- No FFI edge cases\n- Full algebraic reasoning about hashes\n\n## Algorithm Overview\n\nSHA-256 processes data in 512-bit (64-byte) blocks:\n1. Pad message to multiple of 512 bits\n2. Initialize eight 32-bit hash values (H0-H7)\n3. For each block: expand to 64 words, apply 64 rounds of mixing\n4. Output final 256-bit (32-byte) hash\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Attestation","SHA256"],"SHA256Hash"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[69,46],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Attestation/SHA256.purs","start":[69,1]},"title":"eqSHA256Hash"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Ord"],"Ord"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Attestation","SHA256"],"SHA256Hash"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[70,48],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Attestation/SHA256.purs","start":[70,1]},"title":"ordSHA256Hash"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Attestation","SHA256"],"SHA256Hash"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[73,25],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Attestation/SHA256.purs","start":[72,1]},"title":"showSHA256Hash"}],"comments":"A SHA-256 hash — 256 bits represented as eight 32-bit words.\n\nStored as Array Int for simplicity. Each Int represents a 32-bit word.\nPureScript Ints are 32-bit on most platforms, which is what we need.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"newtype","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[67,44],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Attestation/SHA256.purs","start":[67,1]},"title":"SHA256Hash"},{"children":[],"comments":"Compute SHA-256 hash of a string (UTF-8 encoded as ASCII bytes)\n\nNote: This assumes ASCII input. For full UTF-8 support, use sha256Bytes\nwith proper UTF-8 encoding.\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Attestation","SHA256"],"SHA256Hash"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[442,31],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Attestation/SHA256.purs","start":[442,1]},"title":"sha256"},{"children":[],"comments":"Compute SHA-256 hash of byte array\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Array"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Attestation","SHA256"],"SHA256Hash"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[405,39],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Attestation/SHA256.pur